3. Component Description
Document Loader

Loads PDF using libraries (PyPDFLoader)

Chunking Strategy

Splits text into chunks (e.g., 500–1000 tokens)

Embedding Model

Converts chunks into vectors (e.g., OpenAI / sentence-transformers)

Vector Store

Stores embeddings → ChromaDB

Retriever

Fetches top-k relevant chunks

LLM

Generates final answer using retrieved context

Graph Workflow Engine

Controls execution flow using LangGraph

Routing Layer

Decides:

Answer directly
Escalate to human
HITL Module

Handles escalation & human response integration

4. Data Flow
Document Flow

PDF → Loader → Chunking → Embedding → ChromaDB

Query Flow

User Query → Embedding → Similarity Search → Retrieve Chunks → LLM → Response

With Routing

Query → Graph →

If confident → Answer
Else → HITL
5. Technology Choices
Why ChromaDB
Lightweight
Easy integration
Fast similarity search
Why LangGraph
Stateful workflows
Conditional routing
Graph-based execution (better than linear pipelines)
LLM Choice
GPT-based / open-source (e.g., LLaMA)
Strong reasoning + contextual understanding
6. Scalability Considerations
Large Documents
Efficient chunking
Metadata indexing
High Query Load
Caching responses
Parallel retrieval
Latency
Reduce chunk size
Limit top-k retrieval
